[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring custom classloaders**\n\nI’m thinking about the need for custom classloaders with interfaces, possibly generated. Using URLClassLoader to point to compiled test classes seems natural, but dynamic class loading is tricky. I might skip that or create sibling child loaders. It's essential to have classes in separate packages compiled into a test jar. My main concern is ensuring public interfaces are loaded correctly while handling unsupported features if native dynamic class loading is involved. We may need to define top-level public interfaces for better organization.\n\n**Examining classloader behavior**\n\nI’m considering whether a URLClassLoader with a null parent will load dependencies. It seems that interfaces don't have dependencies, which might simplify things. If I'm using Mockito.mock with a proxy mock maker, the proxy loader must include org.mockito. For this, the CommonClassLoader would need to load both interfaces. However, the proxy class doesn't necessarily require Mockito classes if the invocation handler type is loaded in the application. It's likely that the proxy can use handlers from any loader, but I need to clarify if the mock should be sealed.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0464754f6c923ec10169f9225053b481a2a776a0ad8d3f0998\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-SJZtRNCnnRf1FXMDpwlx5cUCcJ8VS0nk4ky29cmm-kKpOxBYctZEUUkvuBqvO96GiwXBPQxhlJhnKaZKwlnyp_kM673La9MwNBO218gI24h2O08oCQ6Z4QBggr28dUUHh-LFakIXXP2nxAmxjn3Tv8G4IlZlXgw3Jwh1WhPJ8lBGxf8ju2-csB129o9keLTeer-4XiBl7UVdyw3GHoxxHLR-t-bQWS10TcFhm9HcWc70Kaara-3C5j8D8EW8sADSVNDP4OW6-yNjz2NSiwlwnXzolE5nm0rqQ43a-DiPKozxRJIAsmQkdG_JEijGpqSStzQUpa3xxBH8UbYxNc8W1Lg-QtrtDuw2NPx-fku1yIpycIy-cJksjxMPe7eckAZsoXp-X78juX-IXRmyAfEVonWZsO_1hQhsZ16J7pgzMlpAsp59_0gh6lVO1sQbmi7OWuOJPYmSzQU9fG63GTrE8lpxuKzrG5zSu7b9e-QMOUj0OSw-1mdcLYpi1SGWqa-1zGNYWcx6FAbxWNXhcTNjqHrcBD5ncnLJsmdIGU