cZAd4rAxsbfw05l1mWStd740xyoMAGP6Ju7fiG_iJg8jJKwWTw==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring serialization needs**\\n\\nI need a serializable type and could think about creating a mock of SerializableService that extends DynamicAccessService, which is nested in a Serializable way. I'm considering stubbing before serialization and wondering if, when deserialized, it would just echo a default null. Maybe I can use thenReturn to help serialize the handler. I should keep everything organized to assert mock details and I realize I might need object streams as part of this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DqptR67Y4FJToQe1yxn1wDDc|fc_0464754f6c923ec10169f922a5807881a28ad9ca5889143b2b", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/CrossClassLoaderSerializationTestSupport.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mockito.mockito_core;\n\nimport org.mockito.Mockito;\nimport org.mockito.mock.SerializableMode;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.Serializable;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.when;\n\nfinal class CrossClassLoaderSerializationTestSupport {\n    private CrossClassLoaderSerializationTestSupport() {\n    }\n\n    static void serializesAndDeserializesAcrossClassLoaders() throws Exception {\n        SerializableDynamicAccessService service = Mockito.mock(\n                SerializableDynamicAccessService.class,\n                Mockito.withSettings().serializable(SerializableMode.ACROSS_CLASSLOADERS));\n        when(service.echo(\"before serialization\")).thenReturn(\"after serialization\");\n\n        byte[] bytes;\n        try (ByteArrayOutputStream byteStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n                ObjectOutputStream objectStream = new ObjectOutputStream(byteStream)) {\n            objectStream.writeObject(service);\n            bytes = byteStream.toByteArray();\n        }\n\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes))) {\n            Object deserialized = objectStream.readObject();\n\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(deserialized).isMock()).isTrue();\n            assertThat(((SerializableDynamicAccessService) deserialized).echo(\"before serialization\"))\n                    .isEqualTo(\"after serialization\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    interface SerializableDynamicAccessService extends DynamicAccessService, Serializable {\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 354, "output": 522, "cacheRead": 56832, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57708, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777935009122, "responseId": "resp_0464754f6c923ec10169f922a2314481a2beefeb3f3e7ec55f"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_DqptR67Y4FJToQe1yxn1wDDc|fc_0464754f6c923ec10169f922a5807881a28ad9ca5889143b2b", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1894 bytes to tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/CrossClassLoaderSerializationTestSupport.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777935015139}]}
